article.headline: Stetson 71, Lipscomb 66
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon scored 15 of his team-high 19 points in the final 20 minutes as Stetson overcame a late 10-point deficit to beat Lipscomb 71-66 Monday night. Gordon connected on five of seven second-half shots as the Hatters rallied after trailing 58-48 with 6:58 to play in the Atlantic Sun Conference contest. Stetson converted seven of eight free throws in a 12-1 run to take a 60-59 lead with 4:03 on the clock. Stetson (6-9, 4-4) outscored Lipscomb 23-8 in the last 6:45. Anthony Register had 18 points for the Hatters, including 10-of-14 shooting from the foul line, and Will Holloman had 12 points, nine of which came on 3-of-5 three-pointers. Karl Hollingsworth added 10 points, all in the second half. The Bisons (8-6, 3-4) were led by 19 points from James Poindexter, who was 4-for-8 from 3-point range. LaBrian Lyons and freshman forward Eddie Ard chipped in 10 points each.
